      <p class="tldr__body" id="kitchen-sink-g2-editorial-tldr-body">The U.S. small-business accounting market is large, fragmented, and structurally flawed. Most owners choose between three imperfect options: an overworked solo bookkeeper with no continuity, a remote subscription with no accountability, or an offshore team they&rsquo;ll never meet. TechBrot exists to be the fourth option &mdash; <strong>operator accountability</strong> (named, credentialed practices running real engagements) with <strong>platform standards</strong> (vetting, defined operating sequences, quality review, and continuity if anything ever needs to transition). The result is accounting that&rsquo;s accountable to a real practice and backed by a real institution.</p>
