{# ============ process-diagram (trust — four verifiable pillars) ============ #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-g2-editorial-pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The foundation</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Four pillars. All verifiable.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Trust in accounting can&rsquo;t rest on adjectives. It rests on things you can check. These four pillars are the foundation &mdash; each backed by something verifiable, not asserted.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">01</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Credentials</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Certified Intuit QuickBooks ProAdvisors across <strong>all four core platforms</strong> &mdash; QBO Level 2, Desktop, Enterprise, Payroll. Renewed annually through Intuit testing.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>How to verify:</strong> Search Intuit&rsquo;s public ProAdvisor directory at <a href="https://proadvisor.intuit.com" rel="noopener">proadvisor.intuit.com</a> by firm name. Active status = current credentials.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">The ProAdvisor team <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">02</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Accountability</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Every engagement is <strong>fixed-fee with written scope</strong> before any work begins. A <strong>named ProAdvisor owns your account end-to-end</strong> &mdash; same person scopes, delivers, and handles ongoing work.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>How it&rsquo;s structural:</strong> The written scope is the standard. Work that doesn&rsquo;t match is corrected at no cost. No hourly billing, no scope creep, no account-manager rotation.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><a href="/accounting/services/">Engagement standards <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">03</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Security</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">We work as an <strong>accountant-user inside your own QuickBooks file</strong> &mdash; your data, your access controls, grantable and revocable by you at any time. <strong>No data export to a parallel system.</strong></p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>What protects you:</strong> Encrypted screen-share and file transfers. QuickBooks audit trail visible to you at all times. Access logged. You hold the keys.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><a href="/legal/dpa/">Data processing terms <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">04</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Independence</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">TechBrot is an <strong>independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</strong> &mdash; not paid by Intuit or any software vendor. If a different tool fits a client&rsquo;s business better, we say so. Independent ProAdvisor firm, not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Advice follows the client&rsquo;s interest, not a vendor commission. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><a href="/legal/disclaimer/">Independence &amp; disclaimer <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

