{# ============ legal-doc body (about — why a platform, not a firm) ============ #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-g2-editorial-platform">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why a platform, not a firm</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A firm scales by hiring. A platform scales by connecting.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>The traditional accounting firm scales by hiring more accountants, opening more offices, and managing more people. Every additional client adds operational overhead. Quality is bounded by the firm&rsquo;s ability to manage its own staff.</p>
      <p>A platform scales differently. TechBrot operates its own lead practice and curates a network of independent practices that already exist. Brand, demand, infrastructure, and standards on one side. Local expertise, market presence, and the personal accountability of running your own practice on the other.</p>
      <p>This model works because the bottleneck in accounting isn&rsquo;t demand &mdash; it&rsquo;s trust. Every U.S. small business needs reliable bookkeeping, and plenty of skilled accountants want to serve them. What&rsquo;s missing is the connective tissue: a brand the client can trust, a standard the work can be held to, and infrastructure that makes the relationship sustainable. <strong>TechBrot is that connective tissue.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============ pull-quote + legal-doc (trust — why no fake reviews) ============ #}
<section class="section" id="kitchen-sink-g2-editorial-reviews-stance">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">On reviews</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Why you won't find fake reviews here.</h2>
    </header>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>A real review program is worth more than a hundred fabricated stars.</p>
    </blockquote>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Most accounting and bookkeeping sites lead with review counts and testimonials. Many are unverified, self-reported, or worse &mdash; fabricated. We&rsquo;ve made a deliberate choice not to play that game.</p>
      <p>TechBrot is building a <strong>verified-review program</strong> with appropriate client consent &mdash; reviews tied to real, documented engagements. Until that program completes, we&rsquo;d rather show you <strong>verifiable facts</strong> than ask you to take unverifiable testimonials on faith:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Active Intuit ProAdvisor certifications</strong> &mdash; checkable on Intuit&rsquo;s public directory.</li>
        <li><strong>Delaware C-Corporation registration</strong> &mdash; TechBrot Inc., founded 2023.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent fixed-fee pricing</strong> &mdash; published openly on every service page.</li>
        <li><strong>Honest scope</strong> &mdash; what we don&rsquo;t do, stated as clearly as what we do.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>When verified reviews are ready, they&rsquo;ll be published with the same standard of honesty. <strong>A real review program is worth more than a hundred fabricated stars.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

